# SCSS Styling Conventions

## File Organisation
- Global styles → `src/styles/global.scss`
- SCSS variables → `src/styles/variables.scss` (always import this for vars)
- Breakpoint mixins → `src/styles/responsive.scss`
- Component styles → co-located with component (e.g. `tasks.scss` next to `Tasks.tsx`)

## Always Import Variables First
```scss
// ✅ GOOD
@import "../../styles/variables";

// ❌ BAD — hardcoding colours or values inline
background: #2a3447;
```

## Theme Variables (use these, never hardcode)
| Variable | Value | Usage |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `$main-bg` | `#2a3447` | Page/app background |
| `$soft-bg` | `#384256` | Card/panel background |
| `$main-color` | `white` | Primary text colour |

## Breakpoints (from responsive.scss)
`$sm` 480px · `$md` 768px · `$lg` 1024px · `$xl` 1280px · `$xxl` 1400px

```scss
// ✅ GOOD — use mixin
@media (max-width: $md) {
  .taskList { flex-direction: column; }
}
```

## Class Naming
- Use BEM-like flat class names: `.pageTitle`, `.addForm`, `.taskItem`
- Keep class names descriptive and lowercase with camelCase for multi-word
- Don't use deeply nested selectors (max 3 levels)
